    "collapsible_content_hrwAXd": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_a9Qx44": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What benefits will I get from Just Blue™?",
            "row_content": "<p>Here’s what our community has reported:<br/><br/>High-Definition Focus: More energy for your cells = more brain power, without the stimulation effect.</p><p>Enhanced Endurance: Go the extra mile, literally and figuratively. Whether it's a workout or a workday, enjoy a newfound stamina.</p><p>Decreased inflammation: Methylene blue is a powerful antioxidant that helps your cells clean up and clear out.</p><p>Deeper Meditations: Connect with your inner world more profoundly. Just Blue™ users often find their meditative practices enriched, reaching serene depths with ease.portant product information, shipping policies, payment issues or returns.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_dhCeDF": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What scientific research is the formulation based on?",
            "row_content": "<p>See the many articles we've written on Methylene Blue <a href=\"https://troscriptions.com/search?type=product,page,article&q=methylene%20blue*\">here</a>!</p>",
            "page": "",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_F6pAQL": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Will it turn my mouth blue?",
            "row_content": "<p>If used as a buccal troche, yes. The rate of discoloration varies between 2 to 24 hours.<br/><br/>Warning: In addition to being a star ingredient, methylene blue is a dye. It will temporarily stain your mouth (including your teeth). If you have any concerns about dental work and/or prolonged staining, please consult your dentist. Blue tongue resolution speed will depend on how much you move it around when it is dissolving and the amount you use. There is no quick antidote but if you want to reduce the blue faster we have included tips below.</p><p>---<br/><br/>When methylene blue is reduced, it decolorizes. Reducing agents such as sodium bicarbonate — add 1/4 tsp baking soda in 4 fl oz water and rinse the mouth with it for a few minutes — should reduce the methylene blue. This should be done ideally 5-10 minutes after the troche has fully dissolved. Since the reaction is acid-catalyzed, rinse the mouth with 1 part vinegar, and 1 part water first, right before rinsing with baking soda, which would hasten the decolorizing reaction. We also find that hot liquids help as well!</p>",
            "page": "",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_yMaHXA": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I see the 3rd party testing?",
            "row_content": "<p>Email buccalup@troscriptions.com and we'll be happy to share this with you!</p>",
            "page": "",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_axQQwT": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why does it contain Polyethylene Glycol (PEG)?",
            "row_content": "<p>Polyethylene Glycol is a long-established FDA-approved drug delivery method used around the world, especially by compounding pharmacists. Do not confuse polyethylene glycol with propylene glycol. The latter is antifreeze and will kill you if you drink it…so please don’t do that!<br/><br/>Our formulations use polyethylene glycol that is both non-absorbable and very low dose, meaning that it does not get absorbed into your body and it will not cause GI distress or any of those other symptoms/issues that you may have heard about.</p><p>For more information, please see <a href=\"https://troscriptions.com/blogs/main/polyethylene-glycol-peg\">this article</a> for an in-depth explanation.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_miKGN6": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How many troches am I getting?",
            "row_content": "<p>There are 4 whole troches in each package and each troche can be cut into four quarters. Therefore, one pack can yield up to 16 doses, depending on your personalized needs. The troches are scored for easy titration.</p><p>Start with 1/4 troche to 1/2 troche and increase the dosage until you reach your optimal dose.</p><p>DO NOT exceed more than 4 whole troches in a 24-hour period.</p><p>For Tro+ Blue, the above instructions may not apply. Please follow the directions from your healthcare provider.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_ydwGe9": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is the difference between Blue Cannatine™ & Just Blue™?",
            "row_content": "<p>Blue Cannatine™ contains methylene blue (5 mg per troche), caffeine, nicotine and hemp crystals.</p><p>Just Blue™ contains methylene blue (16 mg per troche).</p><p>We created Just Blue™ based on customer requests for a nootropic that optimizes and enhances mitochondrial function without nicotine or caffeine. Blue Cannatine™ gives you more of a \"kick\" or \"launch\" in energy and focus. With Just Blue™, it is more subtle and sustained energy, focus, and endurance.</p><p>Check out our reviews to see our customers' experiences with both products.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_MitCnp": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are there contraindications for Just Blue™?",
            "row_content": "<p>Do not use methylene blue if you are pregnant, breastfeeding, or have G6PD deficiency.</p><p>Do not use methylene blue if you are taking serotonergic drugs such as selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRI), serotonin and norepinephrine reuptake inhibitors (SNRI), or monoamine oxidase inhibitors (MAOi) without the close supervision of your healthcare provider.<br/>There is also a potential risk for serotonin syndrome when methylene blue is used in combination with “psychedelics” and therefore one should avoid this combination unless, again, directed by your healthcare provider.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        }
      },
